Company Overview of Morgan Stanley Private Bank, National Association



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Morgan Stanley Private Bank, National Association offers banking and credit products and services. The company was formerly known as Morgan Stanley Trust and changed its name to Morgan Stanley Private Bank, National Association in July 2010. The company was founded in 1996 and is based in Purchase, New York. Morgan Stanley Private Bank, National Association operates as a subsidiary of Morgan Stanley Delta Holdings LLC.


